{"model":"practice.question","pk":329,"fields":{"subject":1,"topic":2,"difficulty":"hard","text":"A circle has radius 6. What is the arc length that subtends a central angle of 90\u00b0? (Express in terms of \u03c0)","option_a":"3\u03c0","option_b":"6\u03c0","option_c":"9\u03c0","option_d":"12\u03c0","correct_answer":"A","explanation":"Arc length = (central angle/360\u00b0) \u00d7 2\u03c0r = (90/360) \u00d7 2\u03c0(6) = (1/4)(12\u03c0) = 3\u03c0.","source":"PSAT 8/9 Practice","active":True,"created_at":"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z"}},
